description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a Deputy Directorate Manager to join the Anaesthetics, Theatres &amp; Critical Care Directorate who are looking to appoint an enthusiastic, solution-focused and motivated individual to support the smooth running of services.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a key role in the restoration and transformation agenda of services, working with the Directorate Manager, Matrons and Clinical Lead to ensure optimum and on-going performance in line with corporate and national objectives.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Directorate is both dynamic and forward thinking and you will be joining a busy and high performing team with high aspirations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will support the team in delivering a quality service to our patients; working in a rapidly changing environment and achieving tight deadlines.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants must be able to demonstrate that their level of skill and experience reflect the requirements in the job description and person specification.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Mr Philip Windsor, Directorate Manager on 01782 679242&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NamePhilip WindsorJob titleDirectorate ManagerEmail addressphilip.windsor@uhnm.nhs.ukTelephone number01782 671250Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Tracey Folway - Directorate Secretary - 01782 679237&lt;/p&gt;
